  'b242c335-61b3-4850-9c90-9e780659c097',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Vault Zero Trust Architecture: Segregating Secrets with Dynamic Group Membership$escape$,
  $escape$In a Zero Trust Architecture, access is granted based on least privilege and dynamic conditions. Vault achieves this through dynamic group membership, which allows you to assign policies to groups that are determined at runtime. You can use the `group` entity to create groups and the `dynamic_group` entity to create dynamically assigned groups based on attributes and conditions. To integrate with your existing infrastructure, Vault provides a `transformer` function that enables you to fetch data from external systems and use it to update groups.$escape$,
  $escape$vault write dynamic_group/assign -group=dev-group -condition="attribute."data.secret == "true"$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
